---
import OpenClawLayout from "../../layouts/OpenClawLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/cheatsheet-shared.css";
---

<OpenClawLayout
  title="OpenClaw Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes | changelogs.info"
  description="Get OpenClaw installed and running in 10 minutes. Personal AI agent platform — run your own AI on any messaging app."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="cs-wrapper">

    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__emoji">🐾</div>
      <h1 class="oc-headline cs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="cs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-hero__sub">Up and running in 10 minutes — personal AI agent platform, run your own AI on any messaging app.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-grid">

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">Prerequisites</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Node.js 18+</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Required runtime. Check with <code>node --version</code></p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">npm or Homebrew</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">npm comes with Node.js. Homebrew available on macOS.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">Install</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Option A — npm</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> npm install -g openclaw</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Option B — Homebrew (macOS)</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> brew install openclaw</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">First Run</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">1. Onboard</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw onboard</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Sets up your workspace, config files, and default agent.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">2. Start the gateway</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw gateway start</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Launches the local gateway process that routes messages between channels and agents.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">3. Open the dashboard</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw dashboard</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Opens the browser-based control UI. No messaging app needed yet.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">First Real Task — Connect Telegram</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Add a Telegram channel</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd cs-item__cmd--accent"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw channels add --channel telegram --token $BOT_TOKEN</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Get your bot token from @BotFather on Telegram, then run this command.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Pair your phone</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Scan the QR code in <code>openclaw dashboard</code> to link your personal DM.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Add an agent</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd cs-item__cmd--accent"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw agents add mybot</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Creates an isolated agent with its own workspace and persona.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">What Next?</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/openclaw/cheatsheet/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Cheatsheet →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">All the commands and workflows at a glance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/openclaw/tips/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Tips & Tricks →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Quick wins, hidden features, and common mistakes to avoid.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/openclaw/changelog/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Changelog →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Stay up to date with every release.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/openclaw/configs/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Configs →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Configuration reference and recommended settings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</OpenClawLayout>
